        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "@luukvbaal LGTY ?\r\n\r\n@przepompownia there are limited minutes, and yes sometimes things get lost arbitrarily. To reduce the risk of that,\r\n\r\n- keep the PR rebased (for example in this case there are CI failures, which means a reviewer has to confirm if those are false positives)\r\n    - this also notifies anyone watching all PRs (as I do)\r\n- keep the Problem/Solution + test-case very clear (this PR does a good job there)\r\n    - but the PR title could be greatly improved. as CONTRIBUTING.md notes, the *issue title* is often approximately the best title for a \"fix\" PR. in this case, the PR should be titled `fix(ui2): redundant \"Press Enter...\" when piping visual selection to shell cmd`",
            "created_at": "2026-06-03T10:35:38Z",
